Package com.gridgraph.storage.heap.heapfile.schema

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EdgePrimaryDataHeap
    Representation of heap file for storage of edge primary data.
    Data of an edge is stored separately: primary data means 'from/to vertex id', and 'next edge' for 'from/to vertex', while secondary data means 'previous edge id' for 'from/to vertex' and 'property tuple id'
    EdgePropertiesHeap
    Representation of heap file for storage of edge properties data
    EdgeSecondaryDataHeap
    Representation of heap file for storage of edge secondary data.
    Data of an edge is stored separately: primary data means 'from/to vertex id', and 'next edge' for 'from/to vertex', while secondary data means 'previous edge id' for 'from/to vertex' and 'property tuple id'
    SchemaDataHeap
    An abstract representation of heap file for storage of graph element data, either vertex or element data.
    SchemaHeap
    An abstract representation of heap file for a schema.
    SchemaPropertiesHeap
    An abstract representation of heap file for storage of graph element property data, either property data for vertex or element.
    SchemaPropertiesHeap.Exceptions
    Common exceptions to use with a SchemaPropertiesHeap.
    VertexDegreeDataHeap
    Representation of heap file for storage of vertex degree data.
    VertexPrimaryDataHeap

    VertexPropertiesHeap
    Representation of heap file for storage of vertex properties data
